CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 11, 1967, pg. 13, reads: "COMMITTEE - The hard working committee responsible for the success of the NAACP Women's Auxiliary's second annual dinner dance included this group of ladies. Seated from left: Edna Jones, finance chairman; Barbara Davis, decorations; Helen Wright, publicity, and Jean Fox, hostesses.  Standing from left: Pat Ricker, awards; Anne Saunders, invitations; Peggy Bullard, correspondences; Marilyn Parker, door prizes, and Dolores Stanton, souvenir booklet."Accompanying article reads: "An overflow crowd packed the main ballroom of the Pick-Roosevelt Hotel recently when the Women's Auxiliary of the Pittsburgh Branch  NAACP sponsored its second annual "Daisy E. Lampkin Award" Dinner-Dance..."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of women, seated from left: Edna Jones, Barbara Davis, Helen Wright, and Jean Fox; standing: Pat Ricker, Anne Saunders, Peggy Bullard, Marilyn Ware Parker, and Dolores Stanton, at Women's Auxiliary of NAACP dinner dance, Roosevelt Hotel
